  "description": "A lot of contemporary criticism of AI leans on \"entropy\" as if it were a physical proof that statistical systems must inevitably decay into falsehood. But that reading of entropy is not actually in thermodynamics, information theory, or machine learning. It is a cultural inheritance that predates all three.",
